text: <!channel>: stopped by Eastside Woodworks today to check out some new pieces Joe found. photos: <https://www.dropbox.com/sh/fnm3hx7iq4sgloz/AACj1ihC8hpobFkogsmIarXJa?dl=0> . slab 1 is ~130" long, slab 2 is ~100", we didn't measure slab 3?
slabs 1 and 2 have complete live edges, slab 3 is very spotty live edge
I recommend that we take 1 and 2, and we can either cut them both to ~100 (not going above the fridge), or cut slab 1 in the center and spread the two halves so that they span 140" (over the fridge).
slab 2 even has two live edges! we can pick which one we want to use
